{{#> layout bodyClass="page-homepage"}}

  <div class="hero hero--homepage">
    <div class="u-wrap">
      <h1 class="hero__title">Made to scale better</h1>

      <div class="hero__content">
        <p>Funding Circle's styleguide</p>

        <a href="/current" class="btn--normal btn--secondary-alt">See documentation</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="u-background-2 u-section-separator">
    <div class="u-wrap u-center-text homepage-description">
      <h2 class="u-radius-logo">R A D I U S</h2>

      <p>The purpose of this library is to enable all developers to use the design guidelines set by the Funding Circle design team. With that in mind, we&rsquo;ve built this documentation so that it&rsquo;s easy for anyone to use a collection of variables, mixins, functions and utility classes.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="u-background-3">
    <div class="u-wrap u-center-text u-section-separator homepage-features">
      <div>
        <img src="public/img/hp/sass-logo.svg" alt="Sass">
        <h2>Built with Sass</h2>
        <p>The library is built in Sass, with a strong accent on components. The naming methodologies used are BEM and OOCSS (utility classes).</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <img src="public/img/hp/device-agnostic.svg" alt="Device agnostic">
        <h2>Device agnostic</h2>
        <p>Everything is built with a device agnostic approach. We encourage the developers to use the mixins and functions provided to personalise their UX.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <img src="public/img/hp/configure.svg" alt="Configure">
        <h2>Pre-built customisable components</h2>
        <p>We&rsquo;ve already built components for you to use. You can have out of the box tabs, custom form elements, hero/billboards and many more.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="u-wrap u-section-separator homepage-instructions">
    <h2>Requirements</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>NodeJS</li>
      <li>npm</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How to use</h2>
    <p>You can easily import this repository into your project using bower. Just amend `devDependencies` of your project&rsquo;s bower configuration file with:</p>

    <pre class="markup-example"><code>"devDependencies": { "radius" : "git@github.com:FundingCircle/radius.git#1.0.0" }</code></pre>

    <h2>Import the library</h2>
    <p>Import the `style.scss` file from the `dist` directory of the project.</p>
  </section>
{{/layout}}
